- Hey, Mr. Etesami!
- Rana, missy!

23
00:02:18,834 --> 00:02:19,469
Come on out!

24
00:02:20,102 --> 00:02:22,037
The building's about to collapse.

25
00:02:30,571 --> 00:02:32,874
Woman: The building's falling apart.
Get out of there!

26
00:02:33,707 --> 00:02:35,376
What's going on?

27
00:02:35,909 --> 00:02:38,244
What are you doing here, honey?
Come here, honey.

28
00:02:39,278 --> 00:02:40,349
Why? What's going on?

29
00:02:41,382 --> 00:02:44,785
Mr. Etesami evacuate the building.
It's collapsing. Hurry up!

30
00:02:46,718 --> 00:02:48,253
- Let's go, everyone!
- Rana! Rana!

31
00:02:48,455 --> 00:02:50,535
- What's going on, Emad?
- Come here, Rana! Hurry up!

32
00:02:50,836 --> 00:02:52,936
Nasim! Nasim! Gimme the baby!

33
00:02:53,424 --> 00:02:55,724
Let's go, man!

34
00:02:56,457 --> 00:02:59,624
- What's going on, Mr. Fallah?
- I don't know. Just evacuate, man!

35
00:03:00,658 --> 00:03:03,394
Rana! Hurry up! Come on!

36
00:03:05,227 --> 00:03:07,162
- What is it?
- Go down! Go, go!

37
00:03:08,595 --> 00:03:12,130
- Nasim! Chop, chop, Nasim!
- Mr. Amiri, let's go! Evacuate!

38
00:03:14,405 --> 00:03:19,058
Emad, son! Emad!
For God's sake, someone help my baby.

39
00:03:19,284 --> 00:03:20,557
I'm coming, wait.

40
00:03:21,633 --> 00:03:23,033
Here, here, put this on.

41
00:03:23,165 --> 00:03:26,165
- What? Let me come with you.
- No, you can't. Just go down to the alley.

42
00:03:26,304 --> 00:03:29,025
- Go tell everyone to go to the alley.
- Mrs. Samimi! Mrs. Samimi!

43
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:32,740
- Where's Hossein?
- I can't get him out of there.

44
00:03:37,341 --> 00:03:38,641
Hossein, get up!

45
00:03:38,731 --> 00:03:42,940
Hossein, get up, my boy!
The house is coming down.

46
00:03:42,966 --> 00:03:45,659
Get up, Hossein! Get up!

47
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:50,203
- Emad, come on, everyone's gone.
- Go down to the alley. Go tell everyone.

48
00:03:51,204 --> 00:03:53,824
Mr. Fallah, get everyone
down to the alley.

49
00:03:54,037 --> 00:03:56,574
Come on, Hossein!
What are they doing?

50
00:03:59,807 --> 00:04:03,676
- Glasses... my glasses...
- I'll bring your glasses.

51
00:04:23,177 --> 00:04:29,212
The Salesman
Written and Directed by Asghar Farhadi.

52
00:04:38,045 --> 00:04:42,315
Guys!
There's no need to bring all your stuff.

53
00:04:42,849 --> 00:04:45,118
- We've got everything down in our place.
- Okay.

54
00:04:48,752 --> 00:04:51,687
- I can't find it.
- I don't know, just look around.

55
00:04:51,821 --> 00:04:53,781
- You want me to take these?
- Yeah, thanks a lot.

56
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,859
I thought you were supposed to just
bring your towel and toothbrushes?

57
00:04:55,892 --> 00:04:57,852
The towel and the brushes
are in there too.

58
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,960
- Did you lock the car?
- Yeah.

59
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:05,060
Ah, keys, keys!
Gimme the keys.

60
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:07,460
- Here.
- Put it in my pocket.

61
00:05:08,780 --> 00:05:09,700
Guys!

62
00:05:12,780 --> 00:05:13,738
Hey.

63
00:05:13,740 --> 00:05:13,820
Hey Kati Hi.

64
00:05:13,821 --> 00:05:14,738
What's up, Kati?

65
00:05:14,740 --> 00:05:16,338
You guys are alive?!!

66
00:05:16,340 --> 00:05:18,366
The way Sia said the house
has collapsed...

67
00:05:18,392 --> 00:05:21,345
I thought we'd have to drag
you from under the ruins.

68
00:05:21,820 --> 00:05:23,900
Oh, whoa!
What's going on here?

69
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:26,540
There's smell of gas.

70
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:28,898
It's from last night.

71
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:31,360
Well, then, get your stuff.
Let's get out of here.

72
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:35,960
Hey.

73
00:05:36,460 --> 00:05:37,938
Why did you come up?

74
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:40,480
Cut off the electricity,
this is leaking.

75
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:51,981
I can't find the card, man.

76
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,940
Well, see if it's between
your documents and stuff.

77
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:57,900
Kati, dear, don't go
there, it's dangerous.

78
00:05:58,740 --> 00:06:01,000
Oh, my God!

79
00:06:03,220 --> 00:06:06,360
<i>You could only hear the sobbing
of Mashti Hassan's wife,</i>

80
00:06:06,380 --> 00:06:09,461
<i>sitting alone with her lit
lantern on the stable's roof</i>

81
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,980
<i>and the desparate moans of a
cow from inside the stable.</i>

82
00:06:12,540 --> 00:06:14,858
Sir! Is it a true story?

83
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:18,640
True? No, but you could say that
in a way, in Saedi's stories

84
00:06:18,741 --> 00:06:24,838
the scenery, the type of characters,
and relationships are real. Very real.

85
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:26,320
How can someone
turn into a cow, sir?

86
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:27,980
Try looking in the mirror.

87
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:30,280
You think you're funny, huh?

88
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:33,600
But seriously, Sir, how does
a person turn into a cow?

89
00:06:35,380 --> 00:06:36,700
Gradually...

90
00:06:37,260 --> 00:06:39,340
Sir, are we gonna watch the
film of this story too?

91
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,800
Yeah, that's a good idea.

92
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:43,901
Maybe I bring it next time and
we can watch it together.

93
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:44,500
Yes?

94
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:45,980
Sir, when are we gonna
see your play?

95
00:06:46,180 --> 00:06:47,340
The performance begins next week.

96
00:06:47,441 --> 00:06:51,541
Once we've had a few days to settle in,
I'll definitely invite you all to come.

97
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,760
- Thanks, Sir!
- What's it called, Sir?

98
00:06:52,780 --> 00:06:54,220
"Death of a Salesman",
who's read it?

99
00:06:54,340 --> 00:06:55,500
"The Enemy"!

100
00:06:57,540 --> 00:06:59,058
Jokes aside,
have any of you read it?

101
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,938
Sir, who's the author?

102
00:07:00,940 --> 00:07:01,820
Arthur Miller.

103
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:03,540
Hmm... no, I've not.

104
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:05,270
Very good.

105
00:07:05,570 --> 00:07:07,840
Excuse me, boys.

106
00:07:08,420 --> 00:07:09,540
Yes?

107
00:07:10,220 --> 00:07:11,540
Hello.

108
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:13,540
Yes, that's right.

109
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:16,885
Sorry, I can't talk right now,
I'm in class.

110
00:07:16,911 --> 00:07:20,085
If you call back in 10 minutes,
I'll be free.

111
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:24,660
Yeah, with stick shifts... Silver...

112
00:07:26,561 --> 00:07:27,761
Sure... that's fine.

113
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:31,058
Sir, what's your role?

114
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,340
The Salesman.

115
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:35,780
- What are you selling, Sir?
- Potatoes!

116
00:07:35,880 --> 00:07:37,640
When you come,
you'll see for yourselves.

117
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:39,098
What's it's model, Sir?

118
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:40,590
- What?
- Your Peugeot 206, you know.

119
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:43,160
- Why do you wanna know?
- Aren't you selling, Sir?

120
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:46,840
Sir, his dad's a parking officer, just
tell him to scrap your fines for you.

121
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:49,000
Do you even commit
driving offenses, Sir?

122
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:52,060
Sir, why do Iranians call BMWs
"Bee-Em-Veh's"?

123
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:54,340
I didn't hear you.

124
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:57,420
Why do Iranians call BMW's
"Bee-Em-Veh's"?

125
00:07:57,721 --> 00:08:00,921
- Get outa here!
- Dude, just zip it!

126
00:08:01,860 --> 00:08:06,498
That's alright.
He doesn't know, so he's asking.

127
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:08,040
I don't know either.

128
00:08:09,860 --> 00:08:12,200
Guys... eh,
for your next session...

129
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:18,080
I want a summary of this story.
I don't want any excuses, like...

130
00:08:18,081 --> 00:08:21,681
"I fell asleep, we had guests",
and... stuff like that.

131
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:35,200
Mister, could you please
scooch over a bit?

132
00:08:46,260 --> 00:08:49,620
Sir, can I sit in front and
this young man sits back here?

133
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:18,420
Father...

134
00:09:19,140 --> 00:09:20,340
Somebody in there?

135
00:09:21,220 --> 00:09:24,900
No, I think the noise
was from the next door.

136
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:28,381
- No, no, somebody got in your bathroom!
- No, there's no one there.

137
00:09:28,540 --> 00:09:32,098
It’s the next room, there’s a party.
These kind of noises are normal...

138
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:33,900
Can I come out?

139
00:09:35,501 --> 00:09:38,542
There’s something moving
in the bathtub, Willy!

140
00:09:41,380 --> 00:09:45,006
Ah, Miss Francis, you better
go back to your room.

141
00:09:45,032 --> 00:09:47,778
They must be finished painting
by now.

142
00:09:47,780 --> 00:09:49,418
But I can't, I’ve got to
get dressed first!

143
00:09:49,420 --> 00:09:51,840
Yes, you can, you can! Please!

144
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:55,698
Biff, this is Miss Francis,
my next-door neighbor.

145
00:09:55,700 --> 00:10:00,240
They were painting her room.
And she asked to come and use the bath.

146
00:10:00,441 --> 00:10:04,941
And I said, that's alright.
So, I let her take a shower here.

147
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,060
You can go back to your room now.

148
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,658
But, Willy, I don't have any clothes on!

149
00:10:07,660 --> 00:10:10,440
Please, get out of here!
Go back to your room.

150
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:12,900
You promised me stockings, Willy!

151
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,880
I have no stockings here!

152
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:17,600
Why? You had two boxes of size 9s
for me, and I want them, Willy!

153
00:10:17,980 --> 00:10:20,580
Alright, take one and go.
For God’s sake, will you get outa here!

154
00:10:21,081 --> 00:10:22,081
Please!

155
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:23,180
Go!

156
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:40,420
I just hope there’s nobody in the hall.
I can't go out without any clothes!

157
00:10:44,420 --> 00:10:50,100
By the way, are you...
football or...

158
00:10:52,140 --> 00:10:53,420
Dammit!

159
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:55,420
Siavash!

160
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,520
What happened, mom?

161
00:10:57,620 --> 00:10:59,270
I do my best to ignore it but he
keeps getting worse every night!

162
00:10:59,296 --> 00:11:00,145
Sadra, dear, come
down, let's go!

163
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,840
Sanam, dear, just ignore him.

164
00:11:01,940 --> 00:11:03,938
He thinks just because I'm playing a
whore, he can do whatever he wants.

165
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:05,260
- What's that got to do with it?

166
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,000
Why don't you laugh at
the others then, huh?

167
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,774
I was laughing at your
clothes, not you...

168
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,005
Shut up! Shut the hell up!

169
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:11,600
Siavash, come here!

170
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:14,060
Sanam, don't be childish on
this final night. Sanam...

171
00:11:14,580 --> 00:11:17,400
- Alright, I'm freaking sorry... I'm sorry.

172
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:21,220
In this cold, rehearsing every night,
with this child. Let's go, honey.

173
00:11:22,020 --> 00:11:23,820
- You just had to
fuck it up, didn't you?

174
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,120
- What's that got to do with us?
It's your own husband.

175
00:11:25,121 --> 00:11:26,121
- Ah, come on!

176
00:11:26,128 --> 00:11:27,218
Let me take the k...

177
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:29,218
Let go!

178
00:11:29,220 --> 00:11:31,218
Sanam, don't...

179
00:11:31,220 --> 00:11:32,578
I said get off!

180
00:11:32,580 --> 00:11:35,318
- I was kidding... I was kidding!
- I said get off!

181
00:11:38,261 --> 00:11:40,141
- I was messing with you.
- Where are you going?

182
00:11:40,860 --> 00:11:44,335
Comes out of the shower
with a raincoat, and says,

183
00:11:44,361 --> 00:11:47,085
"How can I go out
without any clothes?"

184
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:52,060
I can't, man,
it makes me laugh.

185
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:53,820
Go after her or she'll get
annoyed and won't come tomorrow.

186
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:57,800
Don't make me go out without clothes!
I'm shy!

187
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,580
Come on, how can I go out
without any cloth...

188
00:12:00,581 --> 00:12:01,418
Sanam!

189
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:02,980
The guy's totally nuts!

190
00:12:13,540 --> 00:12:14,338
Did you find a place?

191
00:12:14,340 --> 00:12:18,658
60 sq. Meters, 3rd floor, no elevator.
40 mils in front, 600k tomans per month.

192
00:12:18,660 --> 00:12:20,240
- Where?
- Amiratabak.

193
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:23,240
- What sort of a place are you looking for?
- Something temporary...

194
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:26,102
If we can't find anywhere,
we have to bring our stuff,

195
00:12:26,128 --> 00:12:28,065
and live right in the middle
of the stage.

196
00:12:28,140 --> 00:12:31,140
- You free tomorrow afternoon?
- Why?

197
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,460
I'm taking you somewhere.

198
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:35,720
Come on guys... once more from
the top, no interruptions.

199
00:12:39,260 --> 00:12:40,258
You tired?

200
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:42,258
Nope.

201
00:12:42,260 --> 00:12:44,098
Oh, you're here too!

202
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:47,980
Aww kitty! Who's this?

203
00:12:48,981 --> 00:12:50,781
Come here, you!

204
00:12:53,882 --> 00:12:57,482
He's tame... What's up, kitty?

205
00:13:02,660 --> 00:13:04,160
This place is cool!

206
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:34,240
Babak.

207
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,080
Is that the storage room?

208
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:40,080
- Which one?
- This.

209
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,060
No! It's the second bedroom.

210
00:13:42,140 --> 00:13:43,980
- Really?
- Well, yeah.

211
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:46,760
- Isn't it too small?
- It's a two-bedroom!

212
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:47,800
So, it's good?

213
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,980
You're just two people, what do you
need all this space for anyways?

214
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:51,428
Watch your mouth, "two people"!

215
00:13:51,454 --> 00:13:53,765
Who knows, maybe we end
up being three people...

216
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:57,100
Rana, is he serious?

217
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:58,280
No, come on!

218
00:13:58,680 --> 00:14:00,281
- He doesn't look like it.
- Why is that?

219
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:02,001
Is this door locked?
Is it locked?

220
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:06,160
The previous tenant's stuff is in there.
They're supposed to be collecting it.

221
00:14:07,060 --> 00:14:09,720
Don't be scared, kitty, it's just me.
Come here.

222
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:18,360
- How long's it been vacant?
- Three weeks.

223
00:14:26,660 --> 00:14:27,981
What are they doing to this city?

224
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:32,740
I wish we could tear it
all down, and start over.

225
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:36,820
They've already destroyed and rebuilt
it, and look how it's turned out...

226
00:14:37,420 --> 00:14:38,538
Babak?

227
00:14:38,540 --> 00:14:38,979
Yes dear.

228
00:14:38,981 --> 00:14:40,659
God have mercy on us.

229
00:14:40,660 --> 00:14:42,583
When do you think she'll
clear her stuff out?

230
00:14:42,609 --> 00:14:45,385
She promised she'll do it
in the next coupla days.

231
00:14:53,220 --> 00:14:57,860
There's no parking, you'll have
to leave your car on the street.

232
00:14:57,868 --> 00:15:00,138
That's alright. We're selling the car
to pay your mortgage down payment.

233
00:15:00,140 --> 00:15:01,458
Who mentioned money?

234
00:15:01,460 --> 00:15:02,480
Well, either way...

235
00:15:03,140 --> 00:15:04,540
Hello, Hello, Mr. Salimi.

236
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,060
0ne of the good things about this
place is Mr. Shanazari and his wife.

237
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,698
- Hello.
- Hello, how're you doing?

238
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:11,820
- Hello.
- Hello, hello. How do you do, Ma'am?

239
00:15:13,060 --> 00:15:14,920
Babak, which one's the storage?

240
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:16,920
It's here, come, take a look.

241
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:22,720
- Mr. Salimi?
- Yes?

242
00:15:22,721 --> 00:15:24,860
The door's open, take a look.

243
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:30,980
Please. make sure it doesn't
turn out like the last one.

244
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:32,940
- No, come on, I know these guys.
- You said you knew the last ones too.

245
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:34,940
Don't worry about it.

246
00:15:35,540 --> 00:15:38,220
- Babak, what do they do?
- They're my friends, they're into arts.

247
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:38,920
I hope so.

248
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:40,340
It's okay for a few months.

249
00:15:40,820 --> 00:15:45,860
Just make sure he lets us pay him for it.
No favors.

250
00:15:46,460 --> 00:15:49,780
Looks like we've finally
caught a break.

251
00:15:54,940 --> 00:15:56,620
Careful, don't rush.

252
00:15:57,340 --> 00:16:00,120
You need help, Sir?
- No, you go ahead and bring the rest.

253
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,900
Just careful not to
hit the lightbulb.

254
00:16:13,460 --> 00:16:15,740
Sorry, sir, thanks for the help.

255
00:16:18,140 --> 00:16:21,580
- Are the keys here too?
- She took that one room's with her.

256
00:16:28,940 --> 00:16:30,840
Where's Ali?

257
00:16:40,220 --> 00:16:41,299
- Ali!
- Yep?

258
00:16:41,301 --> 00:16:44,240
For God's sake, leave that alone,
I'll call an electrician tomorrow.

259
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:47,320
- It'll only take a second.
- Leave it, man!

260
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:51,360
If she'd said, we wouldn't have
hired the truck and the movers.

261
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:57,460
What can I say? She sounded so
sure that, I didn't think she'd bail on us.

262
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:01,118
So, what's she saying now?

263
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:03,020
Hasn't answered
ever since this morning.

264
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:05,060
Why don't you try
from a different number?

265
00:17:05,840 --> 00:17:07,960
Bring your phone, Rana.

266
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:13,140
We really need that room,
we've brought all our stuff.

267
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:18,360
Yes.

268
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,060
Okay.

269
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:24,300
He's here if you like to
talk to him.

270
00:17:30,060 --> 00:17:31,040
Thanks.

271
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:34,440
Says, she's said all
she has to say to you.

272
00:17:34,980 --> 00:17:35,940
Well, what did she say?

273
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:39,323
That, she's signed the contract on
a new place two days ago,

274
00:17:39,349 --> 00:17:41,525
but the landlord bucked
at the last moment,

275
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:45,641
She's looking for a place, and can't move
her stuff until she finds somewhere.

276
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:50,880
She said to tell you not to let
anyone touch her stuff. Please!

277
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:56,700
Oh, yeah, and she doesn't
want to talk to you again.

278
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:58,800
Any news?
What happened?

279
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,180
I don't know, nothing for now.
Let me take it, Kati.

280
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,860
- Ali!
- Yes?

281
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:07,340
You got a screwdriver
in your car?

282
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:17,220
This is enough stuff
for a bride's dowry!

283
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:19,440
I thought it was just a
few bits and pieces.

284
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:22,560
- Maybe we should leave it.
- It's fine, I'll take the responsibility.

285
00:18:22,561 --> 00:18:25,561
Alright, boys, let's move
those things over there.

286
00:18:33,460 --> 00:18:34,620
Rana...

287
00:18:35,620 --> 00:18:37,820
These are people's belongings.

288
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:40,298
- Huh?
- These belong to someone.

289
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:42,487
What do you want me to do?
It's been 3 days now.

290
00:18:42,580 --> 00:18:45,081
She keeps saying...
"I'm coming today, I'll come tomorrow."

291
00:18:45,140 --> 00:18:45,900
What if she shows up?

292
00:18:45,940 --> 00:18:49,178
Well she should've kept her word then.
Never mind. Come on!

293
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:51,220
Guys, I can't carry anything heavy!

294
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:12,060
Come on, let's eat.

295
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:16,180
Rana, dear!

296
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:16,900
Yes, dear?

297
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:21,060
Honey... the charger.

298
00:19:21,861 --> 00:19:25,961
<i>I'll turn into words,
run through your ears...</i>

299
00:19:25,962 --> 00:19:28,462
<i>I'll turn into thoughts,
stick in your head...</i>

300
00:19:28,562 --> 00:19:31,962
<i>I'll be a Benz,
race under your feet...</i>

301
00:19:31,963 --> 00:19:35,663
<i>I'll be poverty
in your purse...</i>

302
00:19:35,863 --> 00:19:37,963
<i>I'll be a wolf,
raid your herd.</i>

303
00:20:18,580 --> 00:20:21,058
You two, go to the door and
bring over one of those boxes.

304
00:20:21,060 --> 00:20:22,858
Hi guys.

305
00:20:22,860 --> 00:20:24,538
Are these your 206's car parts, Sir?

306
00:20:24,540 --> 00:20:24,939
Put these in front of the principal's
office, tell the librarian to come see me.

307
00:20:24,941 --> 00:20:27,580
Put these in front of the principal's
office, tell the librarian to come see me.

308
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:31,738
Very good guys, I want the
poem memorized for next time.

309
00:20:31,740 --> 00:20:31,859
Okay.

310
00:20:31,861 --> 00:20:32,620
Okay.

311
00:20:32,820 --> 00:20:33,860
Thank you.

312
00:20:34,620 --> 00:20:36,098
Bye, Sir.

313
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:38,100
Bye.

314
00:21:03,820 --> 00:21:05,180
- Bye, Sir!
- So, long.

315
00:21:07,540 --> 00:21:08,818
Thanks Sir.

316
00:21:08,820 --> 00:21:10,820
Goodbye.

317
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:16,040
- Sir, can I say something?
- What?

318
00:21:16,180 --> 00:21:17,940
Sir, I was really pissed off
the other day.

319
00:21:18,340 --> 00:21:19,180
Which day?

320
00:21:19,340 --> 00:21:22,700
The day, that woman
insulted you in the Taxi.

321
00:21:24,460 --> 00:21:25,898
Was it an insult?

322
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:30,018
You know, that she said, she
wants to sit in the front seat.

323
00:21:30,020 --> 00:21:34,538
Sir, after you got out of the car, I
told them that you were my teacher.

324
00:21:34,540 --> 00:21:37,660
And that we all love you so much.
Like, all the guys.

325
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:41,400
- What was your first name, again?
- Amin.

326
00:21:42,500 --> 00:21:48,140
Amin, I'm sure, some guy must've done
something to her in a taxi before...

327
00:21:48,241 --> 00:21:51,341
to make her think
that way about everyone.

328
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:54,658
Don't worry about it, it's just the
first 100 years that are tough.

329
00:21:54,660 --> 00:21:55,578
So long.

330
00:21:55,821 --> 00:21:57,500
- Bye, sir.
- Bye.

331
00:22:35,620 --> 00:22:36,340
Okay.

332
00:22:39,641 --> 00:22:41,441
Of all the time...

333
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:45,460
I don't know what to do with her.

334
00:22:46,140 --> 00:22:46,860
Who?

335
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:48,700
This woman

336
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:51,660
I called to ask when she'll
clear her stuff out.

337
00:22:51,686 --> 00:22:53,738
She got angry,
started threatening...

338
00:22:53,740 --> 00:22:54,900
Over what?

339
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:59,178
"Why did you touch my personal things?
Those were my private stuff...

340
00:22:59,180 --> 00:22:59,938
I'll sue you..."

341
00:22:59,940 --> 00:23:03,038
Last night I was running around, saving her
stuff from the rain, up until morning.

342
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:03,980
Her problem's something else...

343
00:23:04,140 --> 00:23:06,680
- Who Babak, the woman?
- Yeah.

344
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:09,140
When's she coming
to get her stuff?

345
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:11,200
Says, whenever she finds a place.

346
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:17,060
Sadra, darling, come here with me.
Hurry up.

347
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:22,900
Hurry up guys, the audience
will be in in five minutes.

348
00:23:27,901 --> 00:23:29,701
Emad... Emad...

349
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:32,818
They're coming here
again after the performance.

350
00:23:32,820 --> 00:23:37,680
They've approved 3 of the 6 revisions,
there's another three left.

351
00:23:37,681 --> 00:23:39,381
Stay around and talk to them.

352
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:40,879
- Tonight, after the performance?
- Yeah.

353
00:23:40,901 --> 00:23:42,258
If it helps, I'll stay.

354
00:23:42,260 --> 00:23:44,440
Sure, or else they might cancel
the whole show tomorrow.

355
00:23:44,500 --> 00:23:46,540
- How many did they say?
- Three... Guys will you please hurry up!

356
00:23:46,740 --> 00:23:47,620
I'll go, then.

357
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:49,420
Won't you wait around?

358
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:52,160
No, you'll be stuck here
until around midnight.

359
00:23:52,860 --> 00:23:53,900
Take the car, then.

360
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,700
Where are the house keys?

361
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:57,418
In my coat's pocket.

362
00:23:57,520 --> 00:23:59,420
- Have a good performance.
- You too!

363
00:25:38,220 --> 00:25:41,040
Say, on your way back, if
the supermarket's open...

364
00:25:41,041 --> 00:25:43,241
buy something, we've got
nothing for breakfast.

365
00:25:44,780 --> 00:25:47,920
Yes, I said, if it's...
if it's open!

366
00:25:50,420 --> 00:25:53,060
Also, pick up some
hand sanitizer.

367
00:25:54,561 --> 00:25:56,661
Maybe I take a shower
until you get here.

368
00:25:57,040 --> 00:26:01,040
No, not at all, I'm a mess. I haven't
even wiped off my stage makeup.

369
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:07,400
I'll be out soon... soon.

370
00:26:08,301 --> 00:26:10,101
Yup... love you, bye.

371
00:27:03,620 --> 00:27:05,378
- Anything else?
- That's all, thanks.

372
00:27:06,860 --> 00:27:08,418
Be my guest.
Are you paying by card?

373
00:27:08,420 --> 00:27:09,940
No, cash.

374
00:27:21,740 --> 00:27:23,138
- Yes?
- Hello, Ma'am.

375
00:27:23,140 --> 00:27:23,640
Hello.

376
00:27:23,740 --> 00:27:26,018
Good evening, I'm your
upstairs neighbor.

377
00:27:26,020 --> 00:27:29,420
We've just moved in, could
you open the door, please?

378
00:27:30,220 --> 00:27:31,300
Thank you.

379
00:27:48,740 --> 00:27:49,380
Rana!

380
00:27:51,420 --> 00:27:52,300
Rana!

381
00:27:55,220 --> 00:27:56,420
Rana!

382
00:28:25,900 --> 00:28:26,858
Rana!

383
00:28:26,860 --> 00:28:27,978
What happened to you?

384
00:28:27,980 --> 00:28:29,578
Please, step outside, Sir.

385
00:28:29,580 --> 00:28:33,560
You can't be in here, Sir.
We'll call you for the CT scan.

386
00:28:34,260 --> 00:28:35,580
- Wait outside, please.
- Look at me, Rana!

387
00:28:35,700 --> 00:28:40,940
Everything's fine, I'll call
you for the CT scan... Please.

388
00:28:42,740 --> 00:28:46,900
Make sure you change the
locks, first thing tomorrow.

389
00:28:48,060 --> 00:28:51,660
Why? Did someone
get into the house?

390
00:28:51,961 --> 00:28:53,661
I thought she'd fainted,
was dizzy or...

391
00:28:53,780 --> 00:28:55,140
We don't know what happened yet.

392
00:28:55,300 --> 00:28:58,860
All of a sudden we heard shouting
and screaming from upstairs.

393
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:02,740
Not like, normal, not once,
scream after scream...

394
00:29:02,741 --> 00:29:07,541
I told him go upstairs and check, he said,
couples get into fights all the time.

395
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:10,332
Then, we heard some heavy
bangs in the stairs,

396
00:29:10,358 --> 00:29:13,120
I told him "Muhammad, God
knows, something's up."

397
00:29:13,140 --> 00:29:13,640
Who was it?

398
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:17,800
When we reached the stairs, we
just saw someone fleeing up the street.

399
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:20,178
I don't know what happened to his foot,
but, it had bled all over the stairs.

400
00:29:20,180 --> 00:29:23,880
If I'd caught him, 
he'd be dead now.

401
00:29:24,580 --> 00:29:27,720
Then we went upstairs and found
your wife unconscious...

402
00:29:27,721 --> 00:29:29,665
there was blood all over
the bathroom floor.

403
00:29:29,691 --> 00:29:31,246
I dressed her and 
brought her here.

404
00:29:31,300 --> 00:29:34,418
Never mind that, thank God
something worse didn't happen.

405
00:29:34,420 --> 00:29:40,620
Woman, do us a favor, go to the ER,
check if there's any news or something.

406
00:29:41,980 --> 00:29:45,618
Sorry for putting you
to all this trouble.

407
00:29:45,620 --> 00:29:48,060
Have a seat, 
sit down, son.

408
00:29:53,260 --> 00:29:55,680
Was anything missing
from the house?

409
00:29:56,140 --> 00:29:58,900
I don't know.
I didn't notice anything.

410
00:29:59,460 --> 00:30:03,240
I don't think it was a robbery. What
would a thief be doing in the bathroom?

411
00:30:03,820 --> 00:30:05,418
Then, who was it?

412
00:30:05,420 --> 00:30:07,658
The guy was one of
that woman's customers.

413
00:30:07,660 --> 00:30:08,900
Who? What woman?

414
00:30:09,420 --> 00:30:11,580
The woman who lived there
before you moving in.

415
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:16,740
Tell you the truth, she
was kind of messed up...

416
00:30:17,241 --> 00:30:21,141
and I think, the guy came here on
account of her still being there.

417
00:30:33,820 --> 00:30:35,740
Don't close the door, 
Ali's coming up.

418
00:30:35,780 --> 00:30:36,280
Sure.

419
00:30:42,300 --> 00:30:44,340
Come on, lie down.

420
00:30:50,580 --> 00:30:52,900
Grab my sleeve, hold it.

421
00:30:55,580 --> 00:30:56,500
Thanks.

422
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:06,560
Wait, let me take off your scarf.

423
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:10,638
- You want me to add another pillow?
- No

424
00:31:18,060 --> 00:31:20,120
Turn off the light, 
so she can sleep.

425
00:31:20,220 --> 00:31:20,980
Don't turn it off.

426
00:31:23,140 --> 00:31:25,680
- Can I get you anything?
- No, thanks.

427
00:31:33,540 --> 00:31:35,140
Where are you going, Emad?

428
00:31:36,460 --> 00:31:37,418
Darling?

429
00:31:37,420 --> 00:31:38,898
I said, where are you going?

430
00:31:38,900 --> 00:31:41,738
I'm not going anywhere, I'm here.
You need anything?

431
00:31:41,740 --> 00:31:45,460
Nope. 
Leave the door open.

432
00:31:55,300 --> 00:31:56,020
Okay, thanks.

433
00:31:56,660 --> 00:31:59,381
Look, her blood pressure's low,
careful when she's walking.

434
00:31:59,500 --> 00:32:00,380
Thanks for everything.

435
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:02,818
Sit down guys, I'll make
you some breakfast.

436
00:32:02,820 --> 00:32:04,280
No, thanks, we're late.

437
00:32:05,020 --> 00:32:07,700
Come on, you haven't
eaten since last night.

438
00:32:08,220 --> 00:32:12,080
Kati, you wanna stay here, and
make soup or something for them?

439
00:32:12,181 --> 00:32:14,081
- You want me to stay?
- You want Kati to stay?

440
00:32:14,540 --> 00:32:16,220
- No, no.
- You sure?

441
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:19,220
You must be tired.
Go, get some rest.

442
00:32:19,940 --> 00:32:23,380
- Call if you need anything.
- Really, man, just let us know.

443
00:32:24,080 --> 00:32:26,380
- Thanks again for everything, guys.
- Bye

444
00:34:29,540 --> 00:34:34,111
<i>scrap metal... Iron doors...
Aluminum doors...</i>

445
00:34:34,137 --> 00:34:37,565
<i>Fences... Metal dishes...
buying...</i>

446
00:34:42,660 --> 00:34:50,660
<i>scrap metal... lamps... Samovars...
anything, bring it over...</i>

447
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:16,980
Come on, stand here while
I use the bathroom.

448
00:36:29,420 --> 00:36:30,898
What are you doing?

449
00:36:30,900 --> 00:36:34,680
- Leave it, I'll wash it myself, Rana, dear!
- Come and wash it then.

450
00:36:34,700 --> 00:36:36,801
Alright, turn off the water
and come out.

451
00:36:39,820 --> 00:36:42,260
Then, come and clean it
before I use it.

452
00:36:42,580 --> 00:36:45,060
The police might 
need to see it.

453
00:36:49,300 --> 00:36:49,980
Yes?

454
00:36:52,300 --> 00:36:53,340
Of course, sorry.

455
00:36:53,540 --> 00:36:54,380
Who was it?

456
00:36:54,980 --> 00:36:56,420
One of the neighbors.

457
00:36:56,460 --> 00:36:58,320
- What did they say?
- I'll be right back.

458
00:37:03,780 --> 00:37:05,100
Sorry.

459
00:37:18,480 --> 00:37:20,598
Sorry for all
the trouble, ma'am.

460
00:37:20,600 --> 00:37:23,560
Now, come on, don't say that.
If you ask me, you better call 110...

461
00:37:23,561 --> 00:37:26,161
they'll be able to track
him down from his car.

462
00:37:26,260 --> 00:37:29,660
Yeah, definitely. Anyways,
I'll try to find some place...

463
00:37:30,100 --> 00:37:32,580
I thought, when that woman left,
she took all her troubles with her.

464
00:37:33,060 --> 00:37:35,340
Have you ever seen this
car's owner around here?

465
00:37:35,780 --> 00:37:39,058
Well, it wasn't like, just a
coupla guys visiting her.

466
00:37:39,060 --> 00:37:42,540
I might have to trouble you
again when the police comes...

467
00:37:42,541 --> 00:37:44,661
to explain what you exactly saw.

468
00:37:44,680 --> 00:37:47,058
Yeah, sure. Would you like to
take my cell number?

469
00:37:47,060 --> 00:37:47,978
Yes, please.

470
00:37:47,980 --> 00:37:50,398
- I'll get going.
- Thank you so much, ma'am.

471
00:37:50,520 --> 00:37:53,062
They should tie an ewer
around these guys' necks...

472
00:37:53,088 --> 00:37:55,020
parade them around
the city, shaming them.

473
00:37:55,021 --> 00:37:56,820
0912...

474
00:38:15,220 --> 00:38:17,098
Why are you out here?
Come in.

475
00:38:17,100 --> 00:38:19,340
I'm scared of being
alone in the house.

476
00:38:20,740 --> 00:38:21,940
Where were you?

477
00:38:23,240 --> 00:38:26,700
I went to thank the
neighbors for last night.

478
00:38:27,460 --> 00:38:29,438
- What did they say?
- Nothing.

479
00:38:29,500 --> 00:38:31,498
They asked how you were.

480
00:38:31,500 --> 00:38:35,060
You didn't tell Kati and the
guys what happened, did you?

481
00:38:35,220 --> 00:38:36,300
No.

482
00:38:36,780 --> 00:38:38,820
Okay, I'm going to
the police station...

483
00:38:39,460 --> 00:38:42,500
to file a complaint for them
to start looking for the guy.

484
00:38:42,820 --> 00:38:44,698
How're they gonna find him?

485
00:38:44,700 --> 00:38:46,538
He left his pickup.

486
00:38:46,540 --> 00:38:50,580
And his mobile,
but it's disconnected.

487
00:38:53,020 --> 00:38:54,980
Who was he, Emad?

488
00:38:56,880 --> 00:39:01,140
The neighbors say the woman who
lived here before us, was shady.

489
00:39:01,220 --> 00:39:05,140
The scumbag must've been
one of her customers.

490
00:39:05,141 --> 00:39:06,841
Came here
on account of her.

491
00:39:08,780 --> 00:39:10,540
You remember what he
looked like?

492
00:39:11,060 --> 00:39:12,260
No.

493
00:39:12,900 --> 00:39:14,900
Didn't you get a look at him?

494
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:25,680
It's cold. Come inside,
you'll catch a cold.

495
00:39:38,380 --> 00:39:39,900
Gimme that.

496
00:39:46,380 --> 00:39:48,500
Who got me
out of the bathroom?

497
00:39:50,460 --> 00:39:52,140
One of the neighbors.

498
00:39:52,340 --> 00:39:53,718
Which one?

499
00:39:53,720 --> 00:39:55,900
I don't know, 
just forget it.

500
00:39:59,460 --> 00:40:03,260
Eat your breakfast. And
then go get some rest.

501
00:40:05,980 --> 00:40:10,540
I can't. As soon as I close my
eyes that scene comes to my mind.

502
00:40:19,660 --> 00:40:21,500
How did he get in?

503
00:40:23,780 --> 00:40:26,580
I opened the door,
I thought it was you.

504
00:40:27,500 --> 00:40:32,100
I came out of the bathroom, buzzed
him in, and then went back.

505
00:40:39,100 --> 00:40:43,300
I was shampooing my hair when I
realized someone had come in.

506
00:40:44,580 --> 00:40:47,820
He put his hand in my hair from
behind, I thought it's you.

507
00:40:49,300 --> 00:40:52,660
Then, I saw his hands,
and after that, it's blank.

508
00:41:07,580 --> 00:41:08,820
Rana...

509
00:41:09,740 --> 00:41:12,540
Darling, have some breakfast.

510
00:41:18,260 --> 00:41:19,380
Rana, dear...

511
00:41:21,580 --> 00:41:22,740
Sweetie...

512
00:42:18,780 --> 00:42:20,540
What about tonight's performance?

513
00:42:21,540 --> 00:42:23,740
I called and told them
to cancel it.

514
00:42:23,940 --> 00:42:26,798
- No, call and say I'm coming.
- How? In this condition of yours?

515
00:42:27,060 --> 00:42:29,720
It's harder for me to
stay at home.

516
00:42:34,740 --> 00:42:36,656
Put this on,
let's go to the police station.

517
00:42:36,682 --> 00:42:38,725
We might get held up there
for a while anyways.

518
00:42:39,140 --> 00:42:40,780
No, leave it.
Let's not go to the station.

519
00:42:40,940 --> 00:42:42,600
We can't just do nothing!

520
00:42:43,980 --> 00:42:46,400
I don't want to go
stand there, and...

521
00:42:46,401 --> 00:42:50,201
tell a bunch of officers or
whoever what happened.

522
00:42:50,220 --> 00:42:53,020
Did something happen
that you can't tell?

523
00:42:54,220 --> 00:42:55,138
No.

524
00:42:55,140 --> 00:42:57,900
Then, don't say anything.
I'll tell 'em myself.

525
00:42:59,100 --> 00:43:00,500
I can't, it'll be too much.

526
00:43:11,100 --> 00:43:13,100
No, this isn't foolish talk, Linda.

527
00:43:13,380 --> 00:43:17,180
When I'm walking in the street,
I clearly feel these things...

528
00:43:17,281 --> 00:43:21,681
They pass me by, but it's as if they're
laughing at me with their eyes.

529
00:43:21,780 --> 00:43:25,260
Why? Why would they laugh at you? Don't
talk that way about yourself, Willy.

530
00:43:26,020 --> 00:43:28,540
Sometimes they pass me by
as if I don't even exist.

531
00:43:29,620 --> 00:43:33,780
As though nobody sees me.
Nobody notices me. Nothing.

532
00:43:39,100 --> 00:43:40,340
Linda?

533
00:43:47,940 --> 00:43:52,620
How long are you going to spend
repairing those socks, huh?

534
00:43:53,140 --> 00:43:55,300
You know it makes me angry.

535
00:43:55,301 --> 00:43:59,301
At least don't do it while I'm
home, talking to you. Okay?

536
00:44:04,560 --> 00:44:10,860
Okay, let's talk about something else,
like, my income.

537
00:44:11,420 --> 00:44:17,500
My never-changing income.
God, this is really ridiculous.

538
00:44:17,640 --> 00:44:19,960
<i>What's wrong with you? Why
aren't you saying your lines?</i>

539
00:44:19,980 --> 00:44:25,260
Willy, darling, you're the most
handsome man in the world to me.

540
00:44:28,700 --> 00:44:33,898
You always say this to me, Linda,
always, but it doesn't help me at all.

541
00:44:33,900 --> 00:44:36,258
I'll never be able to make
you happy, you know why?

542
00:44:36,260 --> 00:44:40,500
Because, I'm just a salesman.
I'm nothing! Nothing, Linda!

543
00:44:40,620 --> 00:44:45,180
But, I always tried... why
are you crying, anyways?

544
00:44:49,060 --> 00:44:50,580
Wait, where are you going?

545
00:44:51,540 --> 00:44:53,060
Linda, come back...

546
00:44:58,380 --> 00:45:02,860
Sorry, I have to stop the play.
I apologize to you all.

547
00:45:03,220 --> 00:45:06,358
My wife, the other actor,
isn't feeling well.

548
00:45:06,384 --> 00:45:08,857
Please, give us a
ten-minute intermission.

549
00:45:08,883 --> 00:45:09,550
Sorry.

550
00:45:13,100 --> 00:45:14,618
Can you carry on?

551
00:45:14,620 --> 00:45:18,580
Carry on what, Kati? Can't you see
she's not well? Go, cancel it.

552
00:45:18,660 --> 00:45:21,420
You wanna go to the other
room and lie down a little?

553
00:45:21,620 --> 00:45:25,180
Alright, guys, let's clear the room.
She's not well.

554
00:45:27,500 --> 00:45:29,338
Sanam, dear.

555
00:45:29,340 --> 00:45:31,218
I'm coming.

556
00:45:31,220 --> 00:45:33,220
Can I get you anything?

557
00:45:38,860 --> 00:45:40,100
Kati darling...

558
00:45:40,540 --> 00:45:42,460
Go and cancel the show.

559
00:45:52,460 --> 00:45:54,460
What happened there?

560
00:45:58,380 --> 00:46:02,380
The way someone in the audience
was staring at me bothered me.

561
00:46:04,860 --> 00:46:08,860
The audience want to watch the play,
of course they'll be looking at you.

562
00:46:08,900 --> 00:46:11,380
Looked at me just like that guy.

563
00:46:17,140 --> 00:46:19,098
I thought you said
you didn't see him.

564
00:46:19,100 --> 00:46:23,300
I'm really unwell, I just
don't know what to do.

565
00:46:26,300 --> 00:46:27,978
Babak, come here a minute.

566
00:46:27,980 --> 00:46:29,500
Coming...

567
00:46:37,700 --> 00:46:39,500
Is she feeling better?

568
00:46:40,260 --> 00:46:43,000
Goddammit, man,
what can I say to you...?

569
00:46:43,001 --> 00:46:46,801
Don't you think you had to let me know
what kind of people used to live there?

570
00:46:46,960 --> 00:46:48,618
- What's happened?
- You're supposed to be my friend.

571
00:46:48,620 --> 00:46:52,500
Seriously, what's happened? What is
it to you who lived there before?

572
00:46:52,740 --> 00:46:55,500
That apartment's infamous
in the whole neighborhood.

573
00:46:55,820 --> 00:46:58,380
- Who's said that?
- Let's say nobody's said anything...

574
00:46:58,381 --> 00:47:01,438
why isn't this woman coming
to collect her stuff?

575
00:47:01,440 --> 00:47:04,620
I just wanted to help.
Remembe last week...

576
00:47:04,621 --> 00:47:07,421
you wanted to
sleep on the set?

577
00:47:07,520 --> 00:47:10,400
Regardless, why did you hide from me
that woman's line of work?

578
00:47:10,580 --> 00:47:11,440
What hiding?

579
00:47:11,580 --> 00:47:14,160
Well, yeah. 
Did you tell me or not?

580
00:47:14,280 --> 00:47:19,778
Was I supposed to pass on to you
some unfounded gossip? To upset you?

581
00:47:19,780 --> 00:47:22,018
Well, what's going, anyways?
What's this all about?

582
00:47:22,020 --> 00:47:23,418
Babak, I'm going

583
00:47:23,420 --> 00:47:24,060
I'm coming.

584
00:47:24,260 --> 00:47:27,600
Go take a look at Rana,
you'll see what this is all about.

585
00:47:27,620 --> 00:47:30,080
They said she slipped
in the bathroom.

586
00:47:32,900 --> 00:47:36,260
We said right in front of you we
might be having a kid in that place.

587
00:47:36,361 --> 00:47:38,041
And you didn't say a word,
what kind of...

588
00:47:38,060 --> 00:47:40,140
You were joking!

589
00:47:40,780 --> 00:47:43,458
If we weren't joking,
would you have told us?

590
00:47:43,460 --> 00:47:46,618
Told you what?
Gimme a break!

591
00:47:46,620 --> 00:47:49,780
Put yourself in my shoes, that same
room we sleep in, each night...

592
00:47:49,781 --> 00:47:54,281
how many strange men have
been with that woman.

593
00:47:54,360 --> 00:47:58,698
Don't take it so hard on yourself.
I haven't cashed your check yet.

594
00:47:58,700 --> 00:48:04,140
Whenever you find another place whose
previous tenants had your approval,

595
00:48:04,166 --> 00:48:05,525
you can move out.

596
00:48:16,620 --> 00:48:17,638
- Hello.
- Hello

597
00:48:17,641 --> 00:48:18,661
How are you doing.

598
00:48:18,820 --> 00:48:23,658
Careful not to slip on the stairs
Mrs. Shahnazari, they're wet.

599
00:48:23,660 --> 00:48:31,018
I was actually going to ask the cleaner
to come early and sort these out.

600
00:48:31,020 --> 00:48:35,258
But, I thought you'd want to report it,
the police might want to see them.

601
00:48:35,260 --> 00:48:37,980
Well, it wasn't such a big deal.

602
00:48:38,260 --> 00:48:41,947
You wouldn't say it
if you'd been there and...

603
00:48:41,998 --> 00:48:45,270
seen the state your wife was in,
on the bathroom floor.

604
00:48:45,940 --> 00:48:49,559
When Mr. Alimoradi opened
the bathroom door,

605
00:48:49,585 --> 00:48:53,098
he thought, God forbid,
your wife was dead.

606
00:48:53,100 --> 00:48:55,900
Say hello for me
to your wife.

607
00:49:01,540 --> 00:49:03,180
Get up, I've made you
some breakfast.

608
00:49:03,420 --> 00:49:05,458
- I'm heading out.
- Wait!

609
00:49:11,060 --> 00:49:13,458
Wait, let me get ready
and come with you.

610
00:49:13,460 --> 00:49:15,420
Where to? I have class.

611
00:49:15,500 --> 00:49:17,180
I know, I'll wait in the car.

612
00:49:17,460 --> 00:49:20,020
It's not just an hour or
two, you'll get tired.

613
00:49:20,220 --> 00:49:21,580
Then, don't go today.

614
00:49:21,600 --> 00:49:22,378
What?

615
00:49:22,380 --> 00:49:24,700
I said, don't go today.

616
00:49:25,020 --> 00:49:27,578
Let's say I don't, what
about tomorrow then?

617
00:49:27,580 --> 00:49:30,178
The day after tomorrow?
It's not gonna work.

618
00:49:30,180 --> 00:49:32,900
I can't stay here alone.

619
00:49:33,900 --> 00:49:36,780
I said, I don't want
to be here alone.

620
00:49:37,140 --> 00:49:38,484
What can I do?

621
00:49:38,510 --> 00:49:43,885
You want me to get you a ticket to
visit your parents for a few days?

622
00:49:44,540 --> 00:49:46,100
Looking like this?

623
00:49:47,580 --> 00:49:49,200
I've made up my mind...

624
00:49:49,201 --> 00:49:54,301
we either have to go to the police,
or forget this altogether.

625
00:49:54,400 --> 00:49:57,858
Okay, forget it, but let's look for
a place, right from today.

626
00:49:57,860 --> 00:49:59,338
Okay, we'll start looking.

627
00:49:59,340 --> 00:50:03,178
But until we find somewhere, you
need to try and pick yourself up.

628
00:50:03,180 --> 00:50:05,138
What?! It's not something
I can control.

629
00:50:05,140 --> 00:50:08,239
You taking your pills, and not staying up
at nights getting worked up about it...

630
00:50:08,265 --> 00:50:09,905
is up to you, isn't it?

631
00:50:10,080 --> 00:50:14,440
Go take a shower.
Here, I'll wait right here.

632
00:50:15,060 --> 00:50:16,980
I don't want to go in
that bathroom.

633
00:50:20,900 --> 00:50:22,818
I'll drop you off at a friend's place.
Use theirs.

634
00:50:22,820 --> 00:50:25,500
Go and tell them we've
come to take a shower?

635
00:50:25,720 --> 00:50:28,640
So, what do you want me to do?

636
00:50:29,940 --> 00:50:31,860
You keep changing your mind.

637
00:50:32,540 --> 00:50:34,795
At night you tell me
not to come near you,

638
00:50:34,821 --> 00:50:37,418
then in the morning you
tell me not to leave you.

639
00:50:37,420 --> 00:50:39,338
Just tell me what the hell
am I supposed to do?

640
00:50:39,340 --> 00:50:39,978
Just go, you're late.

641
00:50:39,980 --> 00:50:42,530
It'll take a couple of weeks
to find a new place.

642
00:50:42,556 --> 00:50:43,167
What?

643
00:50:43,193 --> 00:50:46,445
You're not gonna wash up
with that wound of yours?

644
00:51:04,860 --> 00:51:06,900
Sweetheart!

645
00:51:09,140 --> 00:51:11,898
Just think, it could've 
been worse.

646
00:51:11,900 --> 00:51:14,010
What if a piece of glass
had gone in your eye, or...

647
00:51:14,011 --> 00:51:16,919
your head had been
hit harder? Then...

648
00:51:16,920 --> 00:51:18,960
then, what the hell
would I have done?

649
00:51:19,380 --> 00:51:21,340
I wish my head
had been hit harder.

650
00:51:23,180 --> 00:51:26,260
God forbid! Honey, don't
say things like that.

651
00:52:25,620 --> 00:52:27,580
Hello, Mr. Etesami.

652
00:52:39,660 --> 00:52:42,420
Hello Sir, how are you doing?

653
00:52:43,060 --> 00:52:45,460
Mr. Yeganeh gave me these
books to give them to you.

654
00:52:46,380 --> 00:52:48,860
Be quiet. 
What's so funny?

655
00:52:51,300 --> 00:52:52,418
Why?

656
00:52:52,420 --> 00:52:54,940
He said they're not
suitable for kids.

657
00:52:55,660 --> 00:52:57,380
Quiet!

658
00:52:58,660 --> 00:53:01,620
Mr. Yeganeh decided these weren't
suitable for the kids?

659
00:53:03,020 --> 00:53:04,820
Go, throw them in the trash can.

660
00:53:05,020 --> 00:53:05,738
Why the trash can?

661
00:53:05,740 --> 00:53:08,140
Trash can. Throw them
in the trash can.

662
00:53:18,740 --> 00:53:19,858
Give me your phone.

663
00:53:19,860 --> 00:53:21,138
I don't have a phone, Sir.

664
00:53:21,140 --> 00:53:21,858
Give it to me.

665
00:53:21,860 --> 00:53:22,980
I don't have a cell.

666
00:53:23,540 --> 00:53:25,180
Sir, wait a minute.

667
00:53:28,660 --> 00:53:29,538
Give it to me.

668
00:53:29,540 --> 00:53:31,020
Sir, there's nothing
in it about you.

669
00:53:31,140 --> 00:53:31,938
I want to see what you have.

670
00:53:31,940 --> 00:53:32,858
I've deleted it.

671
00:53:32,860 --> 00:53:34,218
Let me see it.

672
00:53:34,220 --> 00:53:36,018
Sir, please, I've deleted it.

673
00:53:36,020 --> 00:53:39,060
Sir, I have private photos 
in there.

674
00:53:39,300 --> 00:53:40,498
Put your hand down.

675
00:53:40,500 --> 00:53:41,780
That's not fair.

676
00:53:43,460 --> 00:53:44,780
Mr. Etesami?

677
00:53:46,300 --> 00:53:47,700
Sir?

678
00:53:49,300 --> 00:53:53,300
I have personal things on there.
I deleted the video.

679
00:53:55,300 --> 00:53:57,500
On my mother's life, 
I deleted it.

680
00:53:57,740 --> 00:54:01,806
Sir, send it on Telegram, for everyone to see.
It beats watching this movie.

681
00:54:01,820 --> 00:54:04,700
I'll kick you out of the class,
if you say another word.

682
00:54:05,180 --> 00:54:06,098
Mr. Etesami!

683
00:54:06,100 --> 00:54:06,698
Sorry, Sir.

684
00:54:06,700 --> 00:54:07,878
You stay out of this!

685
00:54:08,060 --> 00:54:10,140
I mean all of you.

686
00:54:10,141 --> 00:54:11,941
I'm talking to him.

687
00:54:12,420 --> 00:54:13,900
I deleted it.

688
00:54:14,820 --> 00:54:15,900
Please.

689
00:54:19,580 --> 00:54:21,544
Call your father to come to
the school, he needs to see...

690
00:54:21,545 --> 00:54:23,625
the kind of photos
you have on your cell.

691
00:54:24,940 --> 00:54:27,020
His dad's dead, Sir.

692
00:55:20,340 --> 00:55:22,798
- Hi, sorry about that.
- Hi, no problem.

693
00:55:22,881 --> 00:55:27,673
If it's a hassle for you to keep moving it,
you can leave it in the corner.

694
00:55:27,699 --> 00:55:28,659
Next to the boiler room.

695
00:55:28,660 --> 00:55:32,018
When my husband gets back, he'll
move it to a better place.

696
00:55:32,020 --> 00:55:35,418
I don't want you to keep
going up and down the stairs.

697
00:55:35,420 --> 00:55:38,658
I'm going out for a couple of
hours, you can take my spot.

698
00:55:38,660 --> 00:55:40,698
Don't worry, I'll find
a better place for it.

699
00:55:40,700 --> 00:55:42,418
- Suit yourself.
- Sorry.

700
00:55:42,501 --> 00:55:45,058
If you give me the keys,
I can move it for you.

701
00:55:45,060 --> 00:55:45,740
Thanks.

702
00:55:48,020 --> 00:55:51,818
My wife said, you're not
going to report it.

703
00:55:51,820 --> 00:55:52,458
No.

704
00:55:52,460 --> 00:55:55,778
You're doing the right thing, they won't
do anything, even if they catch him.

705
00:55:55,780 --> 00:56:01,420
And you'll have to explain over
and over why you opened the door

706
00:56:01,421 --> 00:56:03,821
plus trekking back
and forth to the court.

707
00:56:03,920 --> 00:56:05,738
Endless hassle for nothing.

708
00:56:05,740 --> 00:56:10,138
But, he'll probably be back for his car.
Please, call me if he shows up.

709
00:56:10,140 --> 00:56:12,140
I'll sort out that bastard.

710
00:56:25,220 --> 00:56:28,778
I'll take mine out and
then come and park yours.

711
00:56:28,780 --> 00:56:30,538
There's no need,
I'll do it myself.

712
00:56:30,540 --> 00:56:32,020
Okay, then, goodbye. Thanks.

713
00:56:32,700 --> 00:56:34,340
Goodbye.

714
00:57:02,220 --> 00:57:03,018
How's it going?

715
00:57:03,020 --> 00:57:05,378
Hey, you okay?
Is Rana here?

716
00:57:05,380 --> 00:57:07,778
- No, wasn't she with you?
- She's coming on her own.

717
00:57:07,900 --> 00:57:09,700
Any news about the guy?

718
00:57:13,140 --> 00:57:14,620
What guy?

719
00:57:15,600 --> 00:57:19,440
Babak had heard some things
from your neighbors.

720
00:57:21,540 --> 00:57:23,098
Where is he? Is he here?

721
00:57:23,100 --> 00:57:24,178
Babak?

722
00:57:24,180 --> 00:57:25,940
Yep, he's back there.

723
00:57:33,180 --> 00:57:34,380
Hi.

724
00:57:34,500 --> 00:57:35,298
Hi.

725
00:57:35,300 --> 00:57:36,980
Why didn't you tell me yesterday?

726
00:57:38,300 --> 00:57:39,618
What should I have told you?

727
00:57:39,620 --> 00:57:42,240
About the man turning up
the other night.

728
00:57:43,060 --> 00:57:44,760
How's Rana?

729
00:57:45,180 --> 00:57:47,140
