01:13:47,335 --> 01:13:48,835
Why are you adding dialogues?

993
01:13:49,436 --> 01:13:50,136
What did I add?

994
01:13:50,837 --> 01:13:53,037
If you've got a problem with
me, let's sit and talk.

995
01:13:53,238 --> 01:13:55,638
Not on the stage, calling
me, "You degenerate!"

996
01:13:55,639 --> 01:13:58,139
It's neither improvisation, nor
acting, you're insulting me.

997
01:13:58,240 --> 01:13:59,840
What? 
Did I hurt your feeling?

998
01:13:59,841 --> 01:14:01,141
Yeah.

999
01:14:01,642 --> 01:14:04,242
And if you do that one more time, I'll
answer you right in front of everyone.

1000
01:14:04,643 --> 01:14:07,143
Degenerate is the one who speaks
his mind through swearing.

1001
01:14:07,344 --> 01:14:08,144
Didn't know that.

1002
01:14:09,045 --> 01:14:10,245
I'm really sorry.

1003
01:14:26,245 --> 01:14:28,145
Bakery.

1004
01:14:36,746 --> 01:14:37,846
Hello, how're you doing?

1005
01:14:46,047 --> 01:14:51,947
<i>Speaking Azeri.</i>

1006
01:15:01,348 --> 01:15:02,748
What can I do for you?

1007
01:15:03,849 --> 01:15:04,729
Two baguettes, please.

1008
01:15:08,550 --> 01:15:10,550
- You want 'em cut?
- Thanks a lot.

1009
01:15:11,251 --> 01:15:13,651
- That pickup's yours?
- Why?

1010
01:15:13,952 --> 01:15:16,452
There's an officer writing tickets,
from the top of the street.

1011
01:15:17,153 --> 01:15:19,253
Majid, come here,
move the car.

1012
01:15:19,654 --> 01:15:21,854
Before the officer
slaps a ticket on it.

1013
01:15:32,255 --> 01:15:33,655
Soheil, bring the keys.

1014
01:15:38,256 --> 01:15:39,177
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

1015
01:15:40,057 --> 01:15:41,157
Later.

1016
01:15:41,858 --> 01:15:42,658
Bye.

1017
01:15:43,259 --> 01:15:44,659
Here you go, Sir.

1018
01:15:44,760 --> 01:15:45,860
Thanks.

1019
01:16:26,561 --> 01:16:29,061
Thanks, dude.
I'll take a water.

1020
01:16:30,562 --> 01:16:32,262
Hello, mister, sorry
is that your pickup?

1021
01:16:32,863 --> 01:16:33,663
Yeah.

1022
01:16:33,964 --> 01:16:36,464
I had some load, I wanted to
ask you to move it for me.

1023
01:16:36,665 --> 01:16:37,945
Nah, that pickup
is for a store.

1024
01:16:38,366 --> 01:16:39,806
Well, not now,
whenever you're free.

1025
01:16:40,067 --> 01:16:42,308
No, it's just that, 
I do something else. I don't do that.

1026
01:16:42,468 --> 01:16:43,868
Not even Friday?

1027
01:16:43,969 --> 01:16:44,569
Nah.

1028
01:16:44,595 --> 01:16:46,994
You can find pickups at
the top of Haft-e-Tir.

1029
01:16:47,270 --> 01:16:48,030
No, it's just that,

1030
01:16:48,056 --> 01:16:51,095
my stuff are books and paintings,
I was looking for a softopper.

1031
01:16:51,171 --> 01:16:54,271
You know, on account of
rain or things like that.

1032
01:16:54,672 --> 01:16:56,072
I'm really busy.
I don't have time.

1033
01:16:56,373 --> 01:16:59,473
I don't care about the fee. I'll pay. I
just want my stuff to get there safe.

1034
01:16:59,574 --> 01:17:01,474
It's just that, I'm busy.
I can't.

1035
01:17:01,675 --> 01:17:03,995
Majid, come on, man. Help the guy.
Late night or something.

1036
01:17:04,776 --> 01:17:07,776
Well, how about you gimme your number?
I'll call you whenever you say.

1037
01:17:07,877 --> 01:17:10,177
And if you come yourself,
even better.

1038
01:17:10,278 --> 01:17:12,478
Bro, find some time between
your schedule for him.

1039
01:17:15,279 --> 01:17:17,179
Careful not to hit the walls.

1040
01:17:22,280 --> 01:17:24,680
Ah! What're you doing here?

1041
01:17:25,881 --> 01:17:27,881
Come here... kitty...

1042
01:17:31,882 --> 01:17:33,322
Careful with that
not to scratch it.

1043
01:17:34,283 --> 01:17:36,583
Babak, tell 'em to come
have a cup of tea.

1044
01:17:37,184 --> 01:17:39,384
- There's no need for that.
- It's getting cold.

1045
01:17:43,185 --> 01:17:44,985
Where are you taking these?

1046
01:17:45,086 --> 01:17:48,886
I'm taking 'em to my parents' parking lot.
We'll see what happens.

1047
01:17:49,087 --> 01:17:50,287
Won't she come to take 'em?

1048
01:17:50,988 --> 01:17:53,688
She's got problems of her own.
She hasn't found a place yet.

1049
01:18:00,690 --> 01:18:03,090
Get up, Babak wants to take
away that woman's stuff.

1050
01:18:03,891 --> 01:18:04,991
What do you want me to do?

1051
01:18:09,292 --> 01:18:10,892
What's going on
between you two?

1052
01:18:11,193 --> 01:18:13,334
Nothing, let him take 'em.
That's okay with me.

1053
01:18:20,594 --> 01:18:22,894
Hello? Majid?

1054
01:18:23,795 --> 01:18:25,595
It's me, Etesami, 
coupla days ago.

1055
01:18:25,796 --> 01:18:27,496
You free today?

1056
01:18:28,397 --> 01:18:29,397
How about Friday?

1057
01:19:33,897 --> 01:19:34,997
Yeah?

1058
01:19:36,398 --> 01:19:37,198
You?

1059
01:19:40,099 --> 01:19:41,999
Yeah, come on up.

1060
01:20:02,298 --> 01:20:03,698
Hello, can I help you?

1061
01:20:04,099 --> 01:20:07,099
Hello, Sir. You okay? Have
I come to the right place?

1062
01:20:07,400 --> 01:20:09,280
Majid said, there's some
stuff you need to move.

1063
01:20:09,681 --> 01:20:11,801
That's right, come on in.
Why didn't he come himself?

1064
01:20:11,902 --> 01:20:14,802
Well, he was busy,
so he sent me instead.

1065
01:20:16,803 --> 01:20:17,803
- After you.
- You first.

1066
01:20:17,904 --> 01:20:20,204
But, he didn't say anything
about all these stairs.

1067
01:20:21,105 --> 01:20:22,405
With this heart of mine.

1068
01:20:22,505 --> 01:20:23,845
Well, if I knew you're coming,

1069
01:20:23,871 --> 01:20:26,730
I would've told him about the
stairs, and the broken elevator.

1070
01:20:27,006 --> 01:20:31,006
Well, I can't use elevators anyways, Sir.
Would you gimme a glass of water?

1071
01:20:36,207 --> 01:20:37,307
Have you hired movers?

1072
01:20:38,007 --> 01:20:42,107
No, I thought he's coming. And,
we'd take the boxes ourselves.

1073
01:20:42,208 --> 01:20:44,108
Well, the poor guy
was kinda busy today.

1074
01:20:45,409 --> 01:20:47,209
- Is he your son?
- Nah, my son-in-law.

1075
01:20:47,310 --> 01:20:49,510
Doesn't make a difference though.
He's like my own son.

1076
01:20:57,411 --> 01:21:01,511
Sorry, old man, we just moved out.
There's no glasses or anything.

1077
01:21:01,812 --> 01:21:03,692
That's alright, mister.
I'll drink from the tap.

1078
01:21:05,713 --> 01:21:06,913
Where are the boxes?

1079
01:21:08,114 --> 01:21:09,214
In that room.

1080
01:21:09,915 --> 01:21:12,315
We'll see. If there's too
many, we'll call movers.

1081
01:21:15,016 --> 01:21:19,216
Give him a call. Maybe he's around
here somewhere. I can pick him up.

1082
01:21:20,017 --> 01:21:21,017
Who?

1083
01:21:21,417 --> 01:21:22,217
Your son-in-law.

1084
01:21:22,918 --> 01:21:26,818
Nah, the poor souls just went shopping
for the "exchange of the vows" ceremony.

1085
01:21:31,519 --> 01:21:33,419
Isn't the janitor
allowed to help here?

1086
01:21:34,020 --> 01:21:35,620
Nah, the building's empty.

1087
01:21:35,721 --> 01:21:38,021
The walls caved, the residents
have all moved out.

1088
01:21:38,122 --> 01:21:40,722
Wow, wow! What if it collapses
on us or something?

1089
01:21:41,023 --> 01:21:41,823
Nah.

1090
01:21:42,024 --> 01:21:44,924
Let's take a look and see if
it's worth hiring movers.

1091
01:21:46,025 --> 01:21:46,825
Grandpa!

1092
01:21:47,726 --> 01:21:48,426
What?

1093
01:21:48,727 --> 01:21:51,827
Would you come sit here for a sec?
I wanna tell you something.

1094
01:21:51,928 --> 01:21:53,828
Look here, mister, this
isn't my line of work.

1095
01:21:53,829 --> 01:21:56,029
Majid said, "there's this guy,
who's called a coupla times...

1096
01:21:56,030 --> 01:21:58,930
would you do it?" I
said, okay, why not?

1097
01:21:58,931 --> 01:22:00,831
Now, you paying depends on
how generous you're feeling.

1098
01:22:00,832 --> 01:22:04,832
Nah, it's not about... wages,
fees, and stuff like that.

1099
01:22:05,233 --> 01:22:08,233
Just sit down. There's
something I have to tell you.

1100
01:22:11,234 --> 01:22:13,134
Good news, I hope.

1101
01:22:16,735 --> 01:22:18,335
How long do you
know this guy?

1102
01:22:19,036 --> 01:22:20,736
- My son-in-law?
- Yeah.

1103
01:22:21,037 --> 01:22:21,737
What for?

1104
01:22:22,038 --> 01:22:23,359
I wanna know
if you know him well.

1105
01:22:24,139 --> 01:22:26,659
Well, it's about two years they've
asked for my daughter's hand.

1106
01:22:27,440 --> 01:22:29,140
Have you asked around
about him?

1107
01:22:31,841 --> 01:22:33,241
Do you know Majid?

1108
01:22:34,842 --> 01:22:36,942
If there's anything you
know, just tell me.

1109
01:22:37,943 --> 01:22:41,843
When my wife and I moved out of
here, we went to a place that...

1110
01:22:43,044 --> 01:22:48,844
its previous tenant was... you
know, a woman of the street.

1111
01:22:50,545 --> 01:22:54,845
One night, when I got home a little late.
My wife was alone in the house.

1112
01:22:55,846 --> 01:22:59,146
One of these lowlifes on account
of that woman still being there...

1113
01:23:00,347 --> 01:23:01,407
enters my house.

1114
01:23:03,848 --> 01:23:05,748
While my wife was
in the bathroom.

1115
01:23:05,949 --> 01:23:07,449
The jerk goes
into the bathroom.

1116
01:23:07,950 --> 01:23:08,750
Who?

1117
01:23:09,251 --> 01:23:10,751
That filthy
son-in-law of yours.

1118
01:23:14,852 --> 01:23:16,852
Now, how do you know
it was Majid?

1119
01:23:17,053 --> 01:23:20,953
When my wife starts screaming, the
guy makes a run for it, but...

1120
01:23:21,854 --> 01:23:24,095
He was in such a hurry that,
he leaves his pickup behind.

1121
01:23:24,455 --> 01:23:26,955
I found him from his pickup. I
went down to where he works.

1122
01:23:28,256 --> 01:23:31,256
I wanted to go there,
grab hold of him...

1123
01:23:33,557 --> 01:23:35,838
and dishonor him in front of
all his co-workers, but...

1124
01:23:38,458 --> 01:23:39,858
I couldn't bring myself
to do it.

1125
01:23:39,959 --> 01:23:42,859
This pickup changes hands
a lot in that store.

1126
01:23:42,860 --> 01:23:44,960
That's why I asked him to come here.
To talk to him, and ask...

1127
01:23:44,961 --> 01:23:47,761
if it was him or
someone else.

1128
01:23:47,762 --> 01:23:48,962
Majid's not like that.

1129
01:23:50,963 --> 01:23:54,063
if I find out it's been him,
I'll call off everything.

1130
01:23:54,164 --> 01:23:55,464
The wedding and all.

1131
01:24:00,005 --> 01:24:01,765
How's your wife, now?

1132
01:24:04,166 --> 01:24:05,666
I don't know what to say.

1133
01:24:09,267 --> 01:24:10,967
Let me talk to him tonight.

1134
01:24:11,068 --> 01:24:13,268
Give him a call and tell
him I wanna talk to him.

1135
01:24:13,369 --> 01:24:15,769
Tell him to come here, I
wanna ask him who's done it.

1136
01:24:15,770 --> 01:24:16,670
Well, it's just,

1137
01:24:16,696 --> 01:24:20,495
they've gone with my wife and daughter
for "the exchange of vows" shopping.

1138
01:24:21,571 --> 01:24:23,071
Well, at least give him a call.

1139
01:24:24,072 --> 01:24:26,472
Ask him who had his pickup
that night.

1140
01:24:27,772 --> 01:24:29,072
When did this happen?

1141
01:24:29,173 --> 01:24:31,773
About two weeks ago.

1142
01:24:33,774 --> 01:24:38,674
Okay, so you just let me
talk to him tonight.

1143
01:24:38,975 --> 01:24:40,275
Oh my... oh my...

1144
01:24:40,875 --> 01:24:42,875
But, I wanna talk to him,
old man.

1145
01:24:43,076 --> 01:24:47,676
Wait a second, I wanna talk to him.
... Call him.

1146
01:24:47,877 --> 01:24:50,077
I don't have his number
in my phone.

1147
01:24:50,478 --> 01:24:51,578
I have it.

1148
01:24:53,679 --> 01:24:56,779
When I say call him to come here,
it's because I don't want to...

1149
01:24:56,780 --> 01:24:58,880
go there, make a scene
in front of his co-workers.

1150
01:24:58,881 --> 01:25:00,981
You just let me
make sure it's him.

1151
01:25:01,482 --> 01:25:04,782
I have to talk to him in such a
way that I'll get an answer...

1152
01:25:04,783 --> 01:25:06,404
How about I call him
myself, huh?

1153
01:25:06,984 --> 01:25:08,984
You want me to do it?

1154
01:25:10,585 --> 01:25:12,285
Okay, let me just
dial his number.

1155
01:25:25,786 --> 01:25:28,986
Hello, Majid? Hi, son...
where are you guys?

1156
01:25:30,287 --> 01:25:32,987
Yeah, I'm here with him.

1157
01:25:35,788 --> 01:25:36,788
Who's with you?

1158
01:25:39,089 --> 01:25:42,989
Listen, when you're alone, gimme a call.
I wanna tell you something.

1159
01:25:45,490 --> 01:25:46,790
Call my cell.

1160
01:25:48,191 --> 01:25:50,891
I don't have it memorized.
Ask Moj'gan.

1161
01:25:53,092 --> 01:25:57,192
Okay... it's nothing... Bye.

1162
01:26:00,193 --> 01:26:02,093
He said, he'll call
when he's alone.

1163
01:26:03,094 --> 01:26:05,294
Say, what do you do yourself?

1164
01:26:06,495 --> 01:26:09,095
I work with this car of Majid's.
His pickup.

1165
01:26:09,596 --> 01:26:12,296
I sell clothes from the back
of the pickup, at nights.

1166
01:26:12,397 --> 01:26:16,097
And I don't come out during the
day, on account of my heart.

1167
01:26:16,098 --> 01:26:17,398
And, how come...

1168
01:26:17,598 --> 01:26:21,498
you don't have your
son-in-law's number?

1169
01:26:21,699 --> 01:26:24,599
Well, I just don't. Not
just him, a lot of people.

1170
01:26:25,100 --> 01:26:27,200
Have you just bought
this number of yours?

1171
01:26:27,501 --> 01:26:28,301
No.

1172
01:26:45,902 --> 01:26:48,802
How come... your son-in-law
doesn't have your number?

1173
01:26:49,803 --> 01:26:52,503
You just told him to get
it from someone else, huh?

1174
01:26:53,004 --> 01:26:54,904
I don't know, man,
I don't know.

1175
01:26:55,005 --> 01:26:57,105
I'm so messed up
right now that...

1176
01:26:57,106 --> 01:26:59,506
I don't even remember
my own name.

1177
01:27:01,906 --> 01:27:03,106
Wait a second, old man.

1178
01:27:03,207 --> 01:27:05,308
- It won't open.
- Not so fast. Wait a minute.

1179
01:27:07,009 --> 01:27:09,009
If it's okay, I want you
to take off your shoes.

1180
01:27:09,610 --> 01:27:10,810
What for?

1181
01:27:11,011 --> 01:27:12,611
I wanna see your foot.

1182
01:27:13,612 --> 01:27:16,012
Mister, I'm as old as your father,
you tellin me to take off my shoes?

1183
01:27:16,113 --> 01:27:17,713
Open the door,
let me go!

1184
01:27:17,914 --> 01:27:19,904
I didn't do anything to you.
Why are you talking like that?

1185
01:27:20,015 --> 01:27:21,715
Take it easy.

1186
01:27:21,816 --> 01:27:24,996
Just take off your shoes for a sec. Then,
I'll open the door for you to leave.

1187
01:27:25,017 --> 01:27:28,317
Why should I take off my shoes?
Open the door!

1188
01:27:28,318 --> 01:27:31,318
Hush! Come here.
Let's go over there.

1189
01:27:41,219 --> 01:27:43,819
Sit on the stair, for a
sec, take off your shoes.

1190
01:27:44,820 --> 01:27:45,320
Sit!

1191
01:27:47,821 --> 01:27:48,421
Sit down!

1192
01:27:51,222 --> 01:27:52,722
Just sit, okay?

1193
01:27:58,423 --> 01:27:59,923
Take off your shoes, please.

1194
01:28:00,224 --> 01:28:01,224
I'm not feeling well,
just don't!

1195
01:28:01,525 --> 01:28:04,025
- Well, let me help you.
- I'll take it off, okay.

1196
01:28:05,727 --> 01:28:07,727
<i>Whispering: I'll take it off.</i>

1197
01:28:15,028 --> 01:28:16,828
The other one,
take off the other one too.

1198
01:28:24,529 --> 01:28:26,029
Your socks too.

1199
01:28:27,730 --> 01:28:29,430
Mister, what do you want from me?

1200
01:28:29,531 --> 01:28:31,431
Take 'em off!
I said, take off your socks.

1201
01:28:31,531 --> 01:28:32,631
Let me do it myself.

1202
01:28:32,832 --> 01:28:35,032
- No!
- Let me! Just let me!

1203
01:29:49,933 --> 01:29:50,933
Hello, Siavash!

1204
01:29:53,934 --> 01:29:55,834
No, I'm a little busy
right now.

1205
01:29:57,335 --> 01:29:59,235
What time is it, anyways?

1206
01:30:00,036 --> 01:30:01,736
No, I'll be there.
Don't worry.

1207
01:30:04,437 --> 01:30:07,737
She'll come herself...
She's a little busy.

1208
01:30:08,324 --> 01:30:09,924
Yeah, I'm okay. I'm fine.

1209
01:30:10,825 --> 01:30:11,925
Okay, bye.

1210
01:30:14,026 --> 01:30:16,926
Swear on my life, I didn't
want to harass anyone.

1211
01:30:18,627 --> 01:30:21,327
Did that woman tell you
to go there that night?

1212
01:30:21,628 --> 01:30:24,528
That woman had been messaging
me for at least a month.

1213
01:30:24,629 --> 01:30:28,609
She said, "If you still have the
pickup, come over, I wanna see you."

1214
01:30:29,430 --> 01:30:32,630
And I messaged back,
"Ahoo, dear, sorry...

1215
01:30:32,731 --> 01:30:34,831
I'm not feeling well.
I can't come.

1216
01:30:35,632 --> 01:30:38,832
She took it to herself. No matter
how many times I called...

1217
01:30:38,933 --> 01:30:41,133
She never answered.

1218
01:30:41,834 --> 01:30:43,234
Didn't want to talk to me.

1219
01:30:43,935 --> 01:30:46,305
That night, I thought I'd drop
by and make it up to her.

1220
01:30:46,436 --> 01:30:48,036
Didn't you know
she's moved out?

1221
01:30:48,237 --> 01:30:50,037
God knows, I had no idea.
Swear on my kids' life...

1222
01:30:50,038 --> 01:30:54,038
You opened the door, and went in. You
saw the furniture is different...

1223
01:30:54,039 --> 01:30:55,559
How come you're saying
you didn't know?

1224
01:30:55,640 --> 01:31:00,040
I went in, I saw a bunch of stuff,
the bicycle I had bought myself...

1225
01:31:01,741 --> 01:31:03,641
I thought maybe she's moving.

1226
01:31:03,642 --> 01:31:05,942
You're not going anywhere
until you tell the truth.

1227
01:31:06,043 --> 01:31:09,383
If I had the slightest idea
that you guys have moved in,

1228
01:31:09,444 --> 01:31:12,444
I would've thought, maybe
there's a man in the bathroom.

1229
01:31:12,645 --> 01:31:15,045
- My wife's clothes were on the bed.
- I didn't saw those.

1230
01:31:15,146 --> 01:31:17,146
You saw those and figured there
must be a woman in the bath.

1231
01:31:17,147 --> 01:31:19,647
All alone, she even
opened the door for you.

1232
01:31:19,648 --> 01:31:21,148
I didn't see any clothes.

1233
01:31:21,549 --> 01:31:24,949
It didn't take even five minutes. I
came in, there was no one there.

1234
01:31:24,950 --> 01:31:27,850
Just a minute ago, your wife
had opened the door for me.

1235
01:31:28,251 --> 01:31:30,151
Why did your wife
open the door for me?

1236
01:31:30,152 --> 01:31:31,852
Well, she thought it's me.

1237
01:31:31,952 --> 01:31:33,952
Let me tell you
what really happened.

1238
01:31:34,053 --> 01:31:38,553
I went by the bathroom door, called
the kid, as soon as I did...

1239
01:31:38,654 --> 01:31:40,454
there starts the screaming.
Then, I ran away.

1240
01:31:40,455 --> 01:31:41,855
You went into the bathroom.

1241
01:31:41,956 --> 01:31:43,556
I didn't go in the bathroom.

1242
01:31:43,657 --> 01:31:45,257
Then, where was your
foot cut like that?

1243
01:31:45,258 --> 01:31:48,858
I have no idea. By the
time I was downstairs...

1244
01:31:48,859 --> 01:31:51,049
I felt a sting in my foot. I thought I've
stepped on something in the stairs.

1245
01:31:51,050 --> 01:31:52,250
Then, my wife's lying?

1246
01:31:52,251 --> 01:31:53,951
Your wife says I went
into the bathroom?

1247
01:31:53,952 --> 01:31:56,099
My wife was scared and
bumped into the glass,

1248
01:31:56,125 --> 01:31:58,852
otherwise God knows what you
would've done, dirty scumbag!

1249
01:31:58,853 --> 01:32:01,953
I swear on my life or
whatever's dear to you...

1250
01:32:01,954 --> 01:32:04,352
as soon as I found out I'm in
the wrong place, I ran away.

1251
01:32:04,354 --> 01:32:08,754
Well, just tell your wife to come here.
Here, I'll wait right here. Ask her.

1252
01:32:08,775 --> 01:32:10,855
What's my wife
supposed to say?

1253
01:32:11,956 --> 01:32:15,356
My wife's said all she had to say.
It's your wife's turn to come here.

1254
01:32:15,557 --> 01:32:17,857
Call her, and tell her
to come here, right now.

1255
01:32:18,558 --> 01:32:19,258
What for?

1256
01:32:19,359 --> 01:32:21,459
What you said, I want you to
repeat in front of your wife.

1257
01:32:21,560 --> 01:32:23,860
Mister, why don't you get it?
I didn't go in that bath...

1258
01:32:23,861 --> 01:32:25,161
Okay, you didn't!

1259
01:32:25,662 --> 01:32:28,662
I want you to tell your wife what
you were doing in that house.

1260
01:32:28,763 --> 01:32:29,763
Call her, right now!

1261
01:32:30,264 --> 01:32:31,664
Get it out, and call her!

1262
01:32:32,165 --> 01:32:33,965
Nope! Get out your cell!

1263
01:32:38,565 --> 01:32:40,965
Don't make me look bad in
front of my wife and kids.

1264
01:32:41,266 --> 01:32:42,266
Call her, right now.

1265
01:32:42,467 --> 01:32:44,367
My daughter's about to
get married.

1266
01:32:44,368 --> 01:32:46,008
Your daughter has to know
her real father.

1267
01:32:46,369 --> 01:32:51,369
I'm gonna tell your son-in-law everything,
just so he knows his father-in-law.

1268
01:32:51,770 --> 01:32:54,470
I don't have to keep you here.
Go on, get out! Go!

1269
01:32:55,571 --> 01:32:59,171
I'm gonna call your son-in-law,
tell him to bring your wife here...

1270
01:32:59,172 --> 01:33:01,172
Leave me alone, mister! Ah!

1271
01:33:07,673 --> 01:33:09,573
Someone help me! Help!

1272
01:33:10,274 --> 01:33:12,674
Don't make noises! Quiet!

1273
01:33:14,175 --> 01:33:15,975
Open the door! Open up!
I'll die!

1274
01:33:17,576 --> 01:33:20,976
I'm about to have a stroke.
Open the door!

1275
01:33:22,077 --> 01:33:26,377
Mister! Open the door! I'm
afraid of closed spaces.

1276
01:33:29,878 --> 01:33:31,078
Open the door, my boy.

1277
01:33:38,979 --> 01:33:40,879
At least turn on the lights.

1278
01:34:06,180 --> 01:34:07,480
Forgive me...

1279
01:34:09,581 --> 01:34:11,181
my dear!

1280
01:34:14,281 --> 01:34:15,981
I can’t cry.

1281
01:34:17,782 --> 01:34:20,282
Why did you ever
do that to yourself?

1282
01:34:24,283 --> 01:34:26,283
I don’t understand it.

1283
01:34:26,984 --> 01:34:29,184
Help me, Willy!

1284
01:34:34,485 --> 01:34:37,185
It seems to me that you’re
just on another trip.

1285
01:34:37,786 --> 01:34:39,486
I keep expecting you.

1286
01:34:45,988 --> 01:34:48,388
I made the last payment
on the house today.

1287
01:34:49,788 --> 01:34:51,288
Right today.

1288
01:34:52,889 --> 01:34:55,689
And there’ll be nobody home.

1289
01:34:58,590 --> 01:35:00,890
We’re free and clear.

1290
01:35:04,291 --> 01:35:06,191
We’re free.

1291
01:36:24,792 --> 01:36:26,692
Rana, lock the door,
and take the keys.

1292
01:36:38,993 --> 01:36:41,193
Get up... on your feet!

1293
01:36:56,994 --> 01:36:58,194
Here, wait.

1294
01:36:59,995 --> 01:37:00,995
Sit here.

1295
01:37:17,196 --> 01:37:18,496
You go in that room.

1296
01:37:47,697 --> 01:37:50,597
Look how mentally and
emotionally shattered she is.

1297
01:37:58,198 --> 01:37:59,608
There's my wife.

1298
01:38:00,198 --> 01:38:02,598
You still gonna say you haven't
gone into the bathroom?

1299
01:38:04,899 --> 01:38:05,699
I'm sorry.

1300
01:38:06,500 --> 01:38:07,600
Answer me.

1301
01:38:10,801 --> 01:38:11,901
I made a mistake.

1302
01:38:12,602 --> 01:38:15,502
Tell me, why did you
go into the bathroom?

1303
01:38:21,103 --> 01:38:22,603
I gave into temptation.

1304
01:38:34,005 --> 01:38:35,605
What are you gonna do to him?

1305
01:38:35,906 --> 01:38:40,106
His family are on their way, I want
his wife to know what he's done.

1306
01:38:48,500 --> 01:38:50,300
You're taking your revenge.

1307
01:38:53,101 --> 01:38:54,701
Let him go, let him leave.

1308
01:38:55,402 --> 01:38:57,102
I know what I'm doing.

1309
01:38:58,503 --> 01:39:00,703
You sit here, there's no
need for you to come out.

1310
01:39:22,504 --> 01:39:24,104
Where are you going?

1311
01:39:26,305 --> 01:39:28,905
I'm not feeling well at all.
Let me go.

1312
01:39:29,506 --> 01:39:30,906
They're coming after you.

1313
01:39:31,407 --> 01:39:33,207
Your son-in-law called,
he asked about you.

1314
01:39:33,308 --> 01:39:34,808
I told him to come over.

1315
01:39:35,009 --> 01:39:36,409
And to bring your wife too.

1316
01:39:37,810 --> 01:39:40,310
They're on their way.
Sit down.

1317
01:39:46,911 --> 01:39:48,511
I'm begging you, please
let me go.

1318
01:39:49,012 --> 01:39:52,812
When your family's here. Tell 'em
everything you told me. Then leave.

1319
01:39:53,114 --> 01:39:54,214
I'm begging you.

1320
01:40:12,615 --> 01:40:13,715
Miss!

1321
01:40:14,916 --> 01:40:16,116
Forgive me.

1322
01:40:16,717 --> 01:40:18,817
Let me go,
before they get here.

1323
01:40:37,317 --> 01:40:39,917
That woman lived with me for
35 years.

1324
01:40:52,918 --> 01:40:54,818
Mister! Get up! Get up, go!

1325
01:40:58,619 --> 01:41:00,419
You, sit down!

1326
01:41:00,719 --> 01:41:01,840
Leave him alone,
let him go.

1327
01:41:02,020 --> 01:41:03,620
He'll go, he will.

1328
01:41:03,821 --> 01:41:06,921
When his family get here,
they can leave together.

1329
01:41:07,121 --> 01:41:08,021
Sit down!

1330
01:41:08,222 --> 01:41:09,922
- For the love of God!
- Here, mister, go.

1331
01:41:10,024 --> 01:41:10,824
- Just, sit down.
- Let him go!

1332
01:41:10,825 --> 01:41:12,225
My girl! My boy!

1333
01:41:12,426 --> 01:41:14,826
- Leave him alone, Emad!
- You stay out of this!

1334
01:41:15,627 --> 01:41:17,927
- Sit down!
- Please.

1335
01:41:18,029 --> 01:41:20,929
I said sit down! Ah!
SIT... DOWN! Here.

1336
01:41:40,731 --> 01:41:43,731
What? What do you want?

1337
01:41:54,832 --> 01:41:55,932
Oh, my God!

1338
01:41:59,733 --> 01:42:00,733
Emad!

1339
01:42:01,134 --> 01:42:03,934
- Does he, by any chance, take
any under-the-tongue pills?

1340
01:42:04,535 --> 01:42:06,635
I searched. There's
nothing in his pockets.

1341
01:42:06,637 --> 01:42:08,437
- What happened?
- Where are you now?

1342
01:42:09,138 --> 01:42:12,738
No, no, get here as soon as you can.
Okay, okay.

1343
01:42:13,439 --> 01:42:15,539
- Was it the Emergency?
- His family. They're coming.

1344
01:42:15,741 --> 01:42:18,941
- Oh, my God!
- Mister! Can you hear me?

1345
01:42:19,142 --> 01:42:21,942
Does he have a pulse? Emad,
can you hear his heartbeat?

1346
01:42:21,943 --> 01:42:24,543
Rana, for God's sake, keep quiet.
Let me see what I'm doing.

1347
01:42:27,644 --> 01:42:28,445
Where are you going?

1348
01:42:28,449 --> 01:42:30,589
He said he's got pills.
Maybe they're in the car.

1349
01:43:01,845 --> 01:43:05,545
Can you hear me?
Open your mouth. Open!

1350
01:43:21,146 --> 01:43:24,046
Mister! Get up!
Can you hear me?

1351
01:43:27,347 --> 01:43:29,847
Oh, God! Oh, God!

1352
01:43:31,548 --> 01:43:33,848
You better now?
You feeling better?

1353
01:43:36,749 --> 01:43:40,449
Breathe! Breathe!
You better, now?

1354
01:43:54,250 --> 01:43:55,550
Don't worry, he's better.

1355
01:43:55,551 --> 01:43:57,251
You didn't call the Emergency?

1356
01:44:00,041 --> 01:44:01,941
No, I was afraid he might be dead.

1357
01:44:09,502 --> 01:44:10,542
Wait a minute!

1358
01:44:13,843 --> 01:44:17,443
If you say anything to his family, I don't
wanna have anything to do with you.

1359
01:44:26,544 --> 01:44:27,944
Yes?

1360
01:44:32,345 --> 01:44:34,745
- Hello.
- The elevator's broken, use the stairs.

1361
01:44:34,846 --> 01:44:36,546
Okay... Come on, ma!

1362
01:44:37,047 --> 01:44:40,947
You go ahead, I can't run
with this pain in my legs.

1363
01:44:45,648 --> 01:44:47,848
Ya Ali!... My dear.

1364
01:44:49,549 --> 01:44:50,649
Come on in. Come in.

1365
01:45:00,050 --> 01:45:03,550
Ya Allah! Dad! Dad!

1366
01:45:04,351 --> 01:45:05,751
How are you dad?

1367
01:45:06,052 --> 01:45:07,752
- Majid!
- What? Come in.

1368
01:45:07,854 --> 01:45:11,554
- Dad! Daddy!
- Thank God, he's fine.

1369
01:45:11,555 --> 01:45:12,755
You okay, dad?

1370
01:45:13,255 --> 01:45:14,255
I'm fine.

1371
01:45:15,056 --> 01:45:17,856
You're okay.
That was such a scare, dad.

1372
01:45:18,457 --> 01:45:19,857
Where's your mother?

1373
01:45:19,858 --> 01:45:21,558
She's in the stairs.
Let me call her.

1374
01:45:21,559 --> 01:45:22,859
Majid, don't call her.

1375
01:45:23,060 --> 01:45:24,940
- Let's go!
- We'll go, dad, just wait a little.

1376
01:45:25,161 --> 01:45:28,839
Majid! If mother doesn't see him, she'd
think something must've happened to him.

1377
01:45:28,865 --> 01:45:29,766
Let her see he's fine.

1378
01:45:29,962 --> 01:45:32,962
Hello, sorry. We were in such a
hurry that we didn't notice you.

1379
01:45:33,863 --> 01:45:34,496
That's alright.

1380
01:45:34,522 --> 01:45:36,588
Sit down, dad. What
are you getting up for?

1381
01:45:36,665 --> 01:45:39,465
I thought mother better come up and
see you, and then we'll leave. Sit.

1382
01:45:40,066 --> 01:45:43,566
We're in no hurry. Let him sit
down until he gets better.

1383
01:45:43,867 --> 01:45:45,567
We're really sorry, mister.

1384
01:45:46,068 --> 01:45:49,968
Dad, just sit down. Can you?

1385
01:45:50,069 --> 01:45:51,369
Yeah, I'm alright.

1386
01:45:51,570 --> 01:45:52,470
Majid!

1387
01:45:54,071 --> 01:45:56,771
What is it, ma? We're here.

1388
01:45:56,972 --> 01:46:00,372
Come. Thank God, dad's
sitting here. He's all right.

1389
01:46:01,073 --> 01:46:04,873
What is, dad? Huh?

1390
01:46:20,774 --> 01:46:23,574
- It's nothing, ma.
- What happened?

1391
01:46:25,875 --> 01:46:26,975
What happened to you?

1392
01:46:33,676 --> 01:46:36,076
Sweetheart, didn't I tell you not to go?

1393
01:46:41,577 --> 01:46:43,877
See what you're doing
to me and yourself?

1394
01:46:45,778 --> 01:46:48,878
Oh, God.
Thank you so much, God!

1395
01:46:50,779 --> 01:46:53,679
God knows, on our way here I
vowed to give away a hundred

1396
01:46:53,680 --> 01:46:56,480
different charities, just to
hear his voice one more time.

1397
01:46:57,581 --> 01:46:58,781
Thank God.

1398
01:47:02,882 --> 01:47:04,782
How many times did
I tell you not to go?

1399
01:47:04,883 --> 01:47:08,883
My dear! I don't want you to work.
I don't!

1400
01:47:09,684 --> 01:47:12,725
Darling, you said, "Majid called,
I have to go, I'll be back soon."

1401
01:47:12,785 --> 01:47:14,585
Soon, you call this "soon"?

1402
01:47:14,786 --> 01:47:16,786
Mom, we have to thank these guys,
they stayed with him all this time.

1403
01:47:16,787 --> 01:47:19,587
Or else, we don't know what
would've happened to dad.

1404
01:47:19,588 --> 01:47:21,888
We really don't know
how to thank you.

1405
01:47:21,889 --> 01:47:25,089
May God give you back, miss.

1406
01:47:25,590 --> 01:47:29,190
He's my whole life, mister.
Thank you so much.

1407
01:47:29,491 --> 01:47:31,291
You gave me my life back.

1408
01:47:31,592 --> 01:47:34,392
He's all I've got.

1409
01:47:35,093 --> 01:47:36,893
Come on, mom, stop it.

1410
01:47:39,294 --> 01:47:40,894
Get up, let's go.

1411
01:47:46,295 --> 01:47:47,895
I'm sorry.

1412
01:47:50,596 --> 01:47:53,037
Did you take all your stuff, dad?
Where's your cellphone?

1413
01:47:53,797 --> 01:47:54,797
Car keys.

1414
01:47:55,297 --> 01:47:57,497
Where's his glasses? Don't
leave without his glasses.

1415
01:47:57,598 --> 01:48:00,998
I've got it... Come here,
I'll give it to you.

1416
01:48:00,999 --> 01:48:02,899
- You go, I'll get it.
- Majid, the glasses...

1417
01:48:02,900 --> 01:48:04,800
No, let him come.
There's...

1418
01:48:05,201 --> 01:48:08,701
this unfinished business
we need to take care of.

1419
01:48:08,901 --> 01:48:10,001
This way.

1420
01:48:10,502 --> 01:48:14,502
What business? You just
saved his life, son.

1421
01:48:15,803 --> 01:48:18,344
No, mister, we've put you
through enough trouble already.

1422
01:48:18,604 --> 01:48:20,104
It's nothing fancy, you know.

1423
01:48:22,004 --> 01:48:23,104
Come on, this way.

1424
01:48:24,305 --> 01:48:26,205
Well, if there's anything
to do, just let me...

1425
01:48:26,706 --> 01:48:29,106
No, let him come himself.
Come on, this way.

1426
01:48:38,107 --> 01:48:39,307
You guys go.

1427
01:48:49,808 --> 01:48:51,708
Majid. Let me...

1428
01:49:36,009 --> 01:49:38,589
How much money did you leave
in the room, that night?

1429
01:49:38,810 --> 01:49:40,610
Huh?

1430
01:49:41,211 --> 01:49:42,812
How much money did you
leave in the room?

1431
01:49:43,812 --> 01:49:44,512
I didn't count.

1432
01:51:00,913 --> 01:51:02,413
What happened, dad?

1433
01:51:03,814 --> 01:51:05,814
What happened to you?
Oh, my God!

1434
01:51:07,515 --> 01:51:09,815
What happened to you?
He's sick again.

1435
01:51:10,116 --> 01:51:13,116
What are these?
Where were these?

1436
01:51:13,517 --> 01:51:15,637
- Come on, sit down a little.
- Is it your heart, dad?

1437
01:51:17,618 --> 01:51:21,118
Let him sit for a while.
Come on, this way.

1438
01:51:22,119 --> 01:51:25,319
We can't leave like this. Majid!

1439
01:51:25,719 --> 01:51:26,819
Majid, hurry up!

1440
01:51:38,620 --> 01:51:40,820
- We're almost there, dad.
- Esmat!

1441
01:51:41,121 --> 01:51:42,621
I'm hear, dear.

1442
01:51:43,722 --> 01:51:45,822
- Esmat!
- Come on, mom.

1443
01:51:46,323 --> 01:51:48,023
Watch it, don't drop him.

1444
01:51:50,824 --> 01:51:53,824
- Esmat! Esmat!
- What? Darling, I'm here.

1445
01:51:54,826 --> 01:51:56,826
What happened to you?
Ya Abalfazl!

1446
01:51:57,827 --> 01:51:59,227
Stretch his legs.

1447
01:51:59,228 --> 01:52:00,728
Dad! Can you hear me?

1448
01:52:04,529 --> 01:52:07,869
- God! Dad! You hear me? Dad!
- Where are his pills?

1449
01:52:09,830 --> 01:52:12,530
Where are his pills?
Search his pockets.

1450
01:52:13,431 --> 01:52:15,631
Stretch his legs! Hurry up!

1451
01:52:15,632 --> 01:52:16,932
God help us!

1452
01:52:18,230 --> 01:52:20,230
Dad, breathe!

1453
01:52:20,631 --> 01:52:22,331
See if his pills are upstairs.

1454
01:52:32,032 --> 01:52:35,832
Miss! Miss! Are my dad's pills here?

1455
01:52:36,633 --> 01:52:38,533
He's got sick again,
he's lying in the stairs.

1456
01:52:48,535 --> 01:52:51,735
Mister, for God's sake, will
you get on the way right away?

1457
01:52:52,336 --> 01:52:55,556
<i>Yes, miss, just give some time
for my colleagues to get there.</i>

1458
01:52:56,236 --> 01:52:59,396
<i>Just follow my instructions. His
legs must be straight, not bent.</i>

1459
01:53:04,837 --> 01:53:05,837
He's lying face up.

1460
01:53:13,738 --> 01:53:15,838
Mister, he's all blue in the face.

1461
01:53:16,839 --> 01:53:20,839
<i>Just keep doing what I told you. If you
